A vintage 1960s Japanese woodblock print style illustration depicting a single origami crane made of layered translucent rice paper sheets, each layer revealing different intricate maze-like patterns beneath. The crane sits on a traditional lacquered wooden desk with subtle steam rising from an unseen tea cup nearby. Behind it, sliding shoji screens cast geometric shadow patterns across the scene. The color palette features muted indigo, warm cream, and touches of vermillion red. Delicate cherry blossom petals drift through the filtered afternoon light, suggesting transition and change. The composition emphasizes the interplay between visibility and concealment, with some maze pathways clearly visible through the paper while others remain hidden in shadow.
